The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 1: The government may provide greater autonomy to 12 state-owned ports by converting them into corporate houses to help them compete better with global players. About ports, there have been some proposals for corporatisation, but it is not divestment. It is conversion of the legal entity structure to corporate structure, shipping secretary K. Mohandas said.                            
	 Mumbai, June 1: Suzlon Energy will raise funds through rights issue to repay its debt. The company has decided to allot two equity shares for every 15 shares held by the existing shareholders on a rights basis.                             
	 Calcutta, June 1: The BSE has allowed trading of 2.7 crore shares of Dunlop India, issued as rights to the shareholders. The BSE said these shares were pari passu with the old equity shares of the company.                             
	 New Delhi, June 1: Delhi High Court has asked mobile operators to submit their account books to the Comptroller and Auditor General, which will check under-reporting of revenue to calculate the licence fee.                            
	 New York, June 1: Hewlett-Packard (HP) aims to boost margins by cutting jobs and reallocating spending to more profitable technology services, shrinking its workforce by a net 3,000 jobs over three years.                                                                                                                          
